280
00:26:06,420 --> 00:26:08,410
No, Mr. Kevin.

281
00:26:08,420 --> 00:26:10,080
I'll have to try it.

282
00:26:28,430 --> 00:26:30,430
Mr. Kevin gave it to me.

283
00:26:30,430 --> 00:26:32,430
I see that you're going to write a new song, right?

284
00:26:32,430 --> 00:26:33,510
Yes.

285
00:26:33,890 --> 00:26:35,500
Take a look at these songs.

286
00:26:35,520 --> 00:26:38,330
They might help inspire you.

287
00:26:39,630 --> 00:26:41,420
Did you write it yourself, Dad?

288
00:26:41,420 --> 00:26:43,680
Yes, it's been a long time since I wrote anything.

289
00:26:44,460 --> 00:26:47,760
But I just write and leave it alone.

290
00:26:47,770 --> 00:26:49,770
I've never offered it anywhere.

291
00:26:50,530 --> 00:26:52,080
Take a look.

292
00:26:53,450 --> 00:26:55,450
I'll take it to Mr. Tee's room.

293
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:04,580
Dad, are you afraid that I won't be as successful as you?

294
00:27:06,310 --> 00:27:09,270
Well, I'm more worried that you will be confused.

295
00:27:10,740 --> 00:27:12,740
If we don't know ourselves,

296
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:15,850
our songs won't be worth listening to.

297
00:27:16,490 --> 00:27:19,840
Dad, are you trying to say something to me?

298
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:24,850
To compose a song, you must use your heart.

299
00:27:25,190 --> 00:27:28,950
Just write what you feel.

300
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:43,560
But if you don't feel anything,

301
00:27:48,390 --> 00:27:49,980
you should ask Jet.

302
00:27:57,020 --> 00:27:58,660
Ask Jet?

303
00:28:04,150 --> 00:28:08,090
Now, Lala is with Ryo, the national husband.

304
00:28:10,490 --> 00:28:11,950
National husband?

305
00:28:14,230 --> 00:28:15,320
They must be crazy!

306
00:28:15,590 --> 00:28:16,760
What?

307
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:19,890
Really, how, how... and how?

308
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:22,350
Look at these two!

309
00:28:26,770 --> 00:28:28,890
What's so cute?

310
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:52,270
♪ What does a person's heart need? ♪

311
00:28:53,000 --> 00:29:01,640
♪ Give too much, give it chaos ♪

312
00:29:02,860 --> 00:29:09,830
♪ Only you care tenderly ♪

313
00:29:10,450 --> 00:29:14,520
♪ Enough for the two of us  ♪

314
00:29:15,150 --> 00:29:19,320
♪ to do a lot right now ♪

315
00:29:21,620 --> 00:29:26,460
♪ Sometimes you're far away, but it's okay ♪

316
00:29:26,460 --> 00:29:30,860
♪ Sometimes you forget me, but I understand ♪

317
00:29:30,860 --> 00:29:39,160
♪ Sometimes you don't notice me, but don't feel be bad ♪

318
00:29:39,380 --> 00:29:43,770
♪ Just think of me once when you don't miss anyone ♪

319
00:29:46,810 --> 00:29:48,750
You seem stressed today.

320
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:53,730
Yeah, I didn't sing very well today.

321
00:29:55,420 --> 00:29:56,810
If someone like you doesn't sing well,

322
00:29:56,950 --> 00:29:59,450
what about a crow voice like mine?

323
00:30:04,090 --> 00:30:09,600
I don't know how good my voice should be.

324
00:30:12,010 --> 00:30:14,410
Just better than yesterday is enough.

325
00:30:14,830 --> 00:30:16,710
You told me yourself, didn't you?

326
00:30:16,830 --> 00:30:19,650
If you keep practicing, you'll slowly get better.

327
00:30:21,250 --> 00:30:22,970
C'mon, let's go eat.

328
00:30:23,450 --> 00:30:26,200
Why eat and gain weight?

329
00:30:26,460 --> 00:30:28,060
Oh, P'Ae.

330
00:30:28,590 --> 00:30:30,590
I didn't have an appointment today, did I?

331
00:30:30,590 --> 00:30:32,660
Sorry, I forgot to tell you

332
00:30:32,660 --> 00:30:35,260
that I booked another acting class for you.

333
00:30:35,380 --> 00:30:36,870
But I...

334
00:30:37,080 --> 00:30:39,070
But... but what?

335
00:30:39,080 --> 00:30:41,620
Hey, Bank. No more buts.

336
00:30:41,750 --> 00:30:44,780
If you're not active now, when can you get an acting job?

337
00:30:47,400 --> 00:30:49,480
Or don't tell me...

338
00:30:49,510 --> 00:30:52,610
you think they will hire you as a model until you die of old age?

339
00:30:53,440 --> 00:30:55,740
It's not like that.

340
00:30:57,280 --> 00:30:58,970
But I don't want to go today.

341
00:30:59,370 --> 00:31:05,020
Must go, how can't you go? Must go. Go now. Fast.

342
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:06,560
Hurry up.

343
00:31:06,570 --> 00:31:08,380
P'Nut, the director, wants to talk to you.

344
00:31:08,450 --> 00:31:10,250
Go, go, go.

345
00:31:10,270 --> 00:31:11,700
I'll be going, Anda.

346
00:32:45,780 --> 00:32:49,850
Every time I go on stage or I'm in front of many people,

347
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:52,320
it's like I have butterflies in my stomach.

348
00:32:54,910 --> 00:32:56,810
Why is this so pitiful?

349
00:33:17,580 --> 00:33:18,660
Thanks.

350
00:33:20,890 --> 00:33:21,720
Hey, Jet.

351
00:33:21,930 --> 00:33:23,800
Listen to the song my dad wrote.

352
00:33:24,450 --> 00:33:26,450
I think melody is good.

353
00:33:42,730 --> 00:33:43,690
It's nice.

354
00:33:43,740 --> 00:33:46,560
Your father is very talented.

355
00:33:47,900 --> 00:33:48,790
Jet,

356
00:33:49,030 --> 00:33:52,140
I feel like my dad is trying to hint at something.

357
00:33:53,140 --> 00:33:54,480
Hint at what?

358
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:55,970
About composing music.

359
00:33:57,510 --> 00:34:01,890
Dad said that if I can't find inspiration, I should ask you.

360
00:35:02,300 --> 00:35:04,300
We don't have any work today, P'Aigo?

361
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:09,460
Actually, I had a photoshoot for a magazine scheduled,

362
00:35:09,460 --> 00:35:11,370
but I canceled it.

363
00:35:11,370 --> 00:35:13,680
because I thought you would be in the hospital longer.

364
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:16,610
After having a break, I really want to work.

365
00:35:17,040 --> 00:35:19,650
We have a photoshoot tomorrow.

366
00:35:19,650 --> 00:35:21,790
The schedule is so long.

367
00:35:21,790 --> 00:35:24,560
Don't cry and beg me for a break.

368
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:27,010
So today, have a good rest.

369
00:35:33,910 --> 00:35:35,060
What's wrong?

370
00:35:35,330 --> 00:35:37,330
You don't seem very happy.

371
00:35:37,330 --> 00:35:39,330
Are you thinking of someone?

372
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:42,630
No.

373
00:35:43,530 --> 00:35:44,380
Sure?

374
00:35:51,420 --> 00:35:53,190
Ok, I'll be leaving.

375
00:35:53,190 --> 00:35:57,420
I have an appointment to talk to a lawyer about the lawsuit.

376
00:36:20,580 --> 00:36:24,020
I'll ask to look at the gym's CCTV later

377
00:36:24,020 --> 00:36:28,220
to make sure the incident wasn't just an accident.

378
00:36:29,100 --> 00:36:31,870
What if it wasn't an accident?

379
00:36:32,360 --> 00:36:35,090
Then, there are many grounds to appeal.

380
00:36:38,550 --> 00:36:39,620
Excuse me.

381
00:36:41,220 --> 00:36:42,450
What's up, Ryo?

382
00:36:42,460 --> 00:36:44,760
P'Aigo, I'll have to trouble you.

383
00:36:49,110 --> 00:36:50,710
Hello Mrs. Aigo.

384
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:56,740
Hey Da, it's time to sign up for the cartoon contest.

385
00:36:57,150 --> 00:36:58,340
What are you going to draw?

386
00:36:58,480 --> 00:36:59,560
Are you ready?

387
00:37:00,160 --> 00:37:02,940
I will draw Lala as usual.

388
00:37:03,110 --> 00:37:05,400
That's your drawing, right? Let me see it.

389
00:37:05,700 --> 00:37:07,570
I don't want you to show you.

390
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:12,470
What is this?

391
00:37:15,250 --> 00:37:17,860
Mouse? Pig?

392
00:37:19,150 --> 00:37:20,620
It's not an animal.

393
00:37:23,850 --> 00:37:25,050
We'll be leaving.

394
00:37:25,210 --> 00:37:26,070
Goodbye, P' Jet.

395
00:37:26,070 --> 00:37:27,260
Bye, bye.

396
00:37:27,260 --> 00:37:28,760
Bye, Anda.

397
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:34,910
Mrs. Aigo called to discuss the lawsuit.

398
00:37:36,210 --> 00:37:39,270
So they're going to sue P'Jet?

399
00:37:40,220 --> 00:37:40,840
No.

400
00:37:41,070 --> 00:37:43,180
As long as you agree to their terms.

401
00:37:44,950 --> 00:37:46,550
What are their terms?

402
00:37:50,550 --> 00:37:51,530
Anda

403
00:37:54,900 --> 00:37:56,210
What happened?

404
00:38:01,290 --> 00:38:03,230
Ryo decided not to sue us.

405
00:38:04,090 --> 00:38:07,670
Hey, we survived this time.

406
00:38:07,670 --> 00:38:08,740
Yes!

407
00:38:09,460 --> 00:38:12,430
But why is Anda upset?

408
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:17,260
P'Aigo agreed under the terms that Anda must work to compensate.

409
00:38:33,340 --> 00:38:34,750
What work?

410
00:38:35,990 --> 00:38:37,060
Photoshoot.

411
00:38:38,350 --> 00:38:39,590
C'mon, again?

412
00:38:42,310 --> 00:38:44,310
I already said that I don't like photoshoots.

413
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:46,390
They're going to force me again.

414
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:48,360
What is he thinking?

415
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:47,560
Don't give up, little hedgehog.

416
00:41:56,210 --> 00:42:00,260
If someone is willing to open up about their fear,

417
00:42:00,890 --> 00:42:04,610
it would be too cruel to not do anything.

418
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:09,020
For this person,

419
00:42:09,500 --> 00:42:11,290
I want him to know

420
00:42:11,790 --> 00:42:15,840
the butterflies aren't as scary as he thought.

421
00:42:20,330 --> 00:42:21,680
Instead...

422
00:42:23,340 --> 00:42:25,460
they're beautiful and amazing.

423
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:27,690
Just like him.
